First, we need to find the symmetric difference (△) between sets A and B. The symmetric difference of two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection. 

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8}
A ∩ B = {}

So, A △ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between the result (A △ B) and set C.

(A △ B) △ C = ({1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8} △ {2, 3, 5, 7})

(A △ B) ∪ C = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8}
(A △ B) ∩ C = {2, 3, 5, 7}

So, (A △ B) △ C = {1, 4, 6, 8}
